
1. Class methods take decorator @classmethod while
   static methods take decorator @staticmethod. Class methods do compulsarily
   has cls as the first parameter, while static method has no such things

2.Class methods have access to class state's but static methods do not, as static methods
do not know anything about the class.

3. Class Methods are generally used as Factory methods, that is, returning class objs.

4. Static methods are used as utility methods

